  "prompt": "I got 753 rank in Aiims and I have not attended to 1 at counseling. will I am eligible for second and third counseling?",
  "response": "In the context of AIIMS (All India Institute of Medical Sciences) counseling, if you did not attend the first round of counseling, you may still be eligible for the second and third rounds. However, eligibility can depend on specific guidelines set by the AIIMS authorities for that particular academic year.\n\nTypically, if you register for counseling and do not attend the first round, you might lose your opportunity for that round but can still participate in subsequent rounds unless otherwise stated. It is crucial to review the official AIIMS counseling guidelines for the year you are applying for, as there can be changes in policies.\n\nTo ensure you have the most accurate and current information, I recommend checking the official AIIMS website or contacting their counseling helpline.",
